messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
It's 291 Stevens Drive, apartment 202.
What is it?
He came into my apartment and I shot him.
You shot someone?
Yes.
Who did you shoot?
Someone just got into my apartment and I shot him.
Okay. Was it a male?
Yes.
Where is he at?
He's in my apartment.
Okay, you're at 291 Stevens Drive, right?
Yes.
Was he breaking into your house?
Yes, he came in with a knife.
You don't know who he was?
No, I don't know.
So he came into your apartment with a knife and tried to attack you?
Yes, he was trying to kill me.
Where is he in the house?
He's in the living room.
Where did you shoot him?
In the living room, by the couch.
Okay, ma'am, we've got everybody on the way, okay? Where is the gun?
It's in the living room, I dropped it.
Where was he when you shot him?
He was by the couch, coming at me.
Okay, calm down. You said the gun is by him?
Yes.
Do you know where you shot him?
No, I don't want to look.
Okay, is this apartment 202?
Yes, apartment 202.
Alright, don't worry, help is on the way. Just stay where you are.
Okay, thank you.
So the door was unlocked and this person came in. Do you live alone?
Yes, I'm the only one here.
Where were you when he came in?
I was in the bathroom, then I heard yelling.
And where did you keep the gun?
The gun was in my bedroom. I ran to get it.
So, after he came in, he was yelling at you and you ran to the bedroom to get the gun?
Yes, and when I turned around, he was coming at me with the knife.
He had a knife and was coming after you?
Yes, he was.
What's your name?
My name is Kat Jackson.
Can you spell your last name?
J-A-C-K-S-O-N.
How old are you, Kat?
Alright, Kat, just stay on the line with me until help arrives, okay?
Okay, thank you.
